HEADWORD: Mesamœboid
<hw>Mes`a*m⟦oe⟧"boid</hw> <pr>(m⟦ecr⟧s`⟦adot⟧*m⟦emac⟧"boid)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Mes-</ets> + <ets>am⟦oe⟧boid</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>One of a class of independent, isolated cells
found in the mesoderm, while the germ layers are undergoing
differentiation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

